32. Quicum illa consuevit prius ?] ‘ But what do you think will be the feelings of the unfortunate man, with whom she had lived before?' This use of ‘consuesco' occurs again in Hecyra iv. 1. 40:

“Nam si is posset ab ea se derepente avellere Quacum tot consuesset annos, non eum hominem ducerem.”

It is best to take ‘illa’ as the nominative case, and to read ‘ quicum! Some editions omit ‘ cum,' aud take ⁸ qui ' as the ablative; but we do not find ‘ consuesco ' in that con- struction.
